HEADWORD: Zobo
<hw>Zo"bo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native name.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A kind of domestic cattle reared in Asia for its
flesh and milk. It is supposed to be a hybrid between the zebu and the
yak.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

